  "prompt": "Is there an app that gives you recipes based on what you have in the fridge?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several apps designed to help you find recipes based on the ingredients you have in your fridge. Here are a few popular ones:\n\n1. **SuperCook**: This app allows you to input the ingredients you have on hand and provides recipe suggestions based on those items.\n\n2. **BigOven**: BigOven lets you enter your ingredients and find recipes. It also has features for meal planning, grocery lists, and leftovers management.\n\n3. **Yummly**: Yummly offers personalized recipe recommendations based on your ingredient list, dietary restrictions, and tastes.\n\n4. **MyFridgeFood**: This is a web-based application where you can check off ingredients you have, and it will suggest recipes accordingly.\n\n5. **Cookpad**: Cookpad is a community-based recipe app that allows you to search for recipes using specific ingredients.\n\nThese apps often have user-friendly interfaces, making it easy to find recipes that fit your needs.",
